column2: Clearest I've seen in 30 years!  Could be the Zebras!!
Partly cloudy- beautiful day- cool breeze from west.  3 boaters and 1 pulling a skier.  Water color greenish water clarity murky- water levels normal.

Sunny- slight breeze from southeast.  Freshwater jellyfish visible in channel.  The leaves are starting to change color.  The water color is greenish- the water levels are 1in. below normal- and the water clarity is clear.
Calm morning- sunny- and no clouds
sunny -secchi hit bottom- saw jelly fish!
